!! Bundled examples

Three examples ship with the plugin:

* [[$:/plugins/rimir/explide/examples/callout-sandbox]] — imports the theme plugin, renders all four callout types
* [[$:/plugins/rimir/explide/examples/mini-app]] — counter app with `+1`/`Reset` buttons using state management
* [[$:/plugins/rimir/explide/examples/component-lab]] — imports components + theme, demonstrates pills facades

Each uses an ad-hoc tiddler named `Output` as the testcase display tiddler.

!! Creating a config tiddler

# Create a new tiddler (e.g., `My Test`)
# Add the field `rri.type` with value `explide/config`
# Save — the IDE interface appears automatically

!! Importing a plugin

# Open the CONFIG tab
# Find your plugin in the vertical list (e.g., `$:/plugins/rimir/components`)
# Check "Include Plugin into Explide?" to import the whole plugin
# Click {{$:/core/images/new-button}} next to individual shadow tiddlers to add them as explide data
# Use the "Bulk import from filter" slider for batch imports

!! Setting up the Output tiddler

# Switch to the ADHOC tab
# Create a tiddler named `Output`
# Write your wikitext content — this is what the testcase Output tab renders
# To use a different name, set `rri.output-tiddler` in the configuration

!! Using `$rri$:` field remapping

When editing an explide data tiddler in the FIELDS tab:

* Add a field named `tags` — this stores `$rri$:tags` on the data tiddler
* In the assembled testcase, the `$rri$:tags` field is remapped to plain `tags`
* This lets you override any field without interfering with TiddlyWiki's field handling

!! Snapshot workflow

# Open an explide data tab and switch to EDITOR
# Click "Take Snapshot" to save the current state
# Make changes to the tiddler
# Switch to DIFF to see what changed since the snapshot
# Click "Restore from Snapshot" to revert to the saved state

!! Using diagnostics

Switch to the DIAGNOSTICS tab to check for:

* Missing imported plugins or tiddlers
* Imported plugins with no shadow tiddlers used
* Snapshots that are older than the current data

